    "$comment": "Per-runtime gates reflect the LLM noise floor of each platform on a multi-tool surface. OpenClaw uses GRAEAE consensus orchestration \u2014 deterministic-ish, expected near-perfect. ZeroClaw and Claude Code are LLM-driven, ~80% noise floor. Hermes historically runs smaller models, ~60% floor.",
